FBIS4-58343 "drnes085_s_94020" FBIS-NES-94-085 Daily Report 3 May 1994 Iran Rial Falls To 2,700 to Dollar Rial Falls To 2,700 to Dollar LD0305105894 Tehran IRNA in English 1044 GMT 3 May 94 LD0305105894 Tehran IRNA English BFN [Text] Tehran, May 3, IRNA -- The major currencies gained strength against rial at money market Tuesday as compared with Monday's rates. The U.S. dollar, German mark and pound sterling, up by rls. 50, 10 and 90, were exchanged at rls. 2,700, 1,640 and 4,040 respectively. Bahar-e Azadi gold coin, 0.235 ounce of 22 carat gold, was sold at rls. 259,000, rls. 3,000 more than Monday.
